The paper deals with algorithmic problems on graphs, specifically the Subset Feedback Vertex Set problem. The paper discusses the problem on several graph classes, including interval graphs, permutation graphs, and co-bipartite graphs. These graph classes are typically studied in the context of computational geometry and graph theory, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the design of polynomial-time algorithms, which is a common theme in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem on various graph classes, which is a topic typically studied in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.CG, and cs.DM, followed by cs.GT and cs.CC.
